items.title: Quality initiatives can reduce harm to newborns, shorten hospital stay and save millions
items.summary: A quality-improvement initiative at a neonatal intensive care unit finds that chest X-rays can be performed just twice weekly, lessening the chances of a breathing tube popping out accidentally, reducing infants' exposure to radiation and saving an estimated $1.6 million per year.

alternate.title: Quality initiatives can reduce harm to newborns, shorten hospital stay and save millions

items.title: 45 percent of parents experience depression, anxiety and stress when newborns leave NICU
items.summary: Almost half of parents whose children were admitted to a neonatal intensive care unit experienced postpartum depressive symptoms, anxiety and stress when their newborns were discharged from the hospital.

alternate.title: 45 percent of parents experience depression, anxiety and stress when newborns leave NICU
